title: (x) "Cafe El Cubano" business card - (similar to) ITC Blair, Fenway Park, Filosofia {Lex}
content:
Does any one know both faces used in the title of this:

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20071017181335im_/http:/typophile.com/files/locubano.jpg)

thank you.

 [‹ (x) serif face in old Premiere magazine issue - FF Scala {Yves}](http://web.archive.org/web/20071017181335/http:/typophile.com/node/18920 "Go to previous forum topic") [(x) Dutch Limousine Service logo - (similar to) Premier {Patricia, Nick Cotrell} ›](http://web.archive.org/web/20071017181335/http:/typophile.com/node/18899 "Go to next forum topic")
author: jondj24

comments.content:
The small text is [Filosofia](http://web.archive.org/web/20071017181335/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/emigre/filosofia/) (and its italic) from Emigre.

The red text looks like Engravers Gothic, Sackers Gothic, or Blair, but the crossbar of the ’A’ is much lower than those fonts, and the top is pointier.

The “cafe” font looks almost like Monotype script. I’ll see if I can find it.

- Lex
